Andrés Bermúdez, also known as the [“Tomato King” because of his invention of
a tomato-planting machine, recently passed away
](http://mexicomonitor.blogspot.com/2009/02/tomato-king-dies-of-stomach-
cancer.html)writes _Mexico Monitor._ Bermúdez also was the first migrant in
the U.S. to become mayor of a Mexican town.

